Study in the UK: Timeline for January 2024 Intake: Deadlines and University Requirements

  • 9223 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Apr 19,2023 12:50 PM IST

The January 2024 Intake in the UK is an excellent opportunity for international students who missed the Fall intake or need more time to prepare their applications to study in the UK. The application window will be open between June and September 2023. Students can research and shortlist universities based on their requirements and preferences, such as location, program of study, budget, and scholarship opportunities. It is essential to take time to make an informed decision and select the university or college that best suits their needs and aspirations.

We have got you covered if you aspire to study in the UK but need details and proper guidance on the admission process and timeline!

If a student chooses to study in the UK, it is essential to know about the three intakes: Fall, Winter, and May. However, the January Intake provides an excellent opportunity for many prospective international students who missed the Fall intake. The Winter or January 2024 Intake in the UK usually runs from January to February. It is an excellent option for students who need extra time to complete their pre-university education during the summer or are still arranging necessary resources.

We understand that the admission process to study in the UK can be overwhelming, so we will also provide a specific timeline for completing the necessary steps and prerequisites to ensure a successful admission to different programs offered by famous UK universities during the January 2024 Intake in the UK.

Let's Find Out More About the January 2024 Intake in the UK:

The January 2023 Intake in the UK is the secondary admission period for UK universities. It is an excellent opportunity for students who missed the main September/Fall Intake or need more time to work on their applications.

The application window for January intake courses will be open between June and September 2023, giving students ample time to gather the necessary documentation and prepare their applications. January 2024 Intake in the UK is less competitive and allows international students to catch up with the September classes.  Remember that the number of courses available during this intake is typically fewer, so it is essential to research the options carefully.

A Step-By-Step Guide on Applying for January 2024 Intake to Study in the UK:

April - June 2023 (Research and Shortlist Universities)

The foremost step to study in the UK is to research and create a list of potential universities and colleges. By doing so, a student can effectively shortlist the preferred universities and courses for further consideration.

1.Determine the requirements for higher education, such as location, program of study, and budget.
2.Research universities and colleges that offer admissions during the January 2024 Intake in the UK and align with your requirements.
3.Shortlist the universities and colleges that meet the criteria to study in the UK. Also, consider scholarship opportunities and financial aid available to international students during the January 2024 Intake in the UK.
4.Narrow the list by shortlisting degrees or disciplines a student wishes to pursue within the selected universities and colleges to study in the UK.
5.Download the respective University brochures or prospectus and read the individual admission requirements and facilities offered during the January 2024 Intake in the UK..
6.Take time to make an informed decision to study in the UK and select the university or college that best suits the needs and aspirations.

Choosing the right university or college is crucial for s student’s academic journey. It is essential to thoroughly research and compare the options before deciding. Good luck with your journey to study in the UK!

June - September 2023  (Appear for Standardized Tests)

If a student plans to study in the UK during the January Intake, knowing the standardised tests required for international students is essential.

English Proficiency Tests Accepted in the UK:

English Proficiency Test
Average Score
TOEFL (Test of English as a Foreign Language)
70 points
IELTS (International English Language Testing System)
6.0 - 7
PTE (Pearson Test English)
54 and above
UCLES (University of Cambridge Local Examinations Syndicate)
180

Indian students are required to take one of the accepted English proficiency tests.

Entrance Exams Accepted in the UK:

Entrance Exam
Average Score
Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT)
600-700
The Graduate Record Examination (GRE)
130-170

The graduate programmes may require scores from GRE or GMAT tests, especially for management, engineering, technology, and architecture courses.

To know the specific admission requirements of the universities, visit their official websites.
To avoid delays in the release of test scores, it is recommended to prepare for and take these tests between June and September 2023. Registration for IELTS and TOEFL should be done at least a month before the test date, while GRE and GMAT should be registered at least three months before the January 2024 Intake in the UK.

It is also advisable to take these tests as early as possible, as they are commonly accepted by universities worldwide, including those in the UK.

September - November 2023 (Submit the Application Forms)

The next step in the admission process to study in the UK is to fill out and submit the application forms to the universities a student has shortlisted. Here are some steps to follow:

1.Visit the official website of the universities shortlisted and fill out the application form with the appropriate information. Make sure to upload all the required documents.
2.Some universities may require students to submit 2–3 Letters of Recommendation and Statements of Purpose or Essays. Ensure to acquire these letters of recommendation at least one month before the application deadline.
3.Structure and form the University Essays or Statements of Purpose at least 2–3 months before the application deadline for the January 2024 Intake in the UK.
4.Submit the letters of recommendation and the SOPS or Essays along with the application forms before the deadline specified by the university for the January 2024 Intake in the UK.

October - November 2023 (Get Acceptance Letters and Respond to the Universities/Colleges)

After submitting the application forms and required documents for the January 2024 Intake in the UK, the universities will contact students for further admission processes. Let us understand how to keep track of the same:

1.Check the registered email ID regularly, as the university's admission committee will contact only through email.
2.Read the emails carefully and follow the instructions given. Each university has a different admission policy, and students should receive a response at least three months before the commencement date of the desired courses to study in the UK.
3.Respond to emails within the deadline and participate in any interviews or selection processes required by the university to study in the UK.
4.Once all the admission processes are complete, the university will send an offer letter if a student gets selected. A non-refundable deposit needs to be made, and students need to follow any other directions given by the university to start their studies in the January Intake in the UK.
Note: Pay the deposit within the given timeline to confirm admission.

November -December 2023 (Apply for a Student Visa and Work on Finances)

Students must arrange their finances and look for scholarship opportunities and financial aid to ensure a smooth admission process for the January 2024 Intake in the UK. Here are some steps to follow:

1.Research and find out about different student loans, scholarships, and financial aid available for international students starting their studies in the January 2024 Intake in the UK. Apply for the appropriate financial assistance to reduce the financial burden.
2.Check if the university, a student has accepted offers scholarships from automatically, or if he/she needs to apply separately for different scholarship opportunities to study in the UK.
3.Settling finances as early as possible is advisable, as last-minute obstacles can negatively impact prospects.

Apply for the Student Visa and Book the Flight to the UK

1.Apply for the correct UK student visas as soon as possible, as the process of confirmation and receiving the same may take time.
2.Search for the best plane tickets at affordable prices as early as possible. Always book tickets early, as they are relatively inexpensive.
3.Always gather all essential documents, including visas, admission letters, and financial records. before heading to the university of your choice to pursue higher education during the January 2024 Intake in the UK.

Why Choose January 2024 Intake to Study in the UK?

Here are a set of reasons to choose the January 2024 Intake to study in the UK:

1.There is less competition during the January Intake, increasing the chances of enrolment at top universities.
2.January Intakes allow students who missed the Fall intake application deadline to not miss out on an entire academic year.
3.January 2024 Intake in the UK is the second intake, and universities offer limited seating and course availability.
4.International students completing their courses during the January 2024 Intake in the UK may have better opportunities as many companies seek new skilled and qualified recruits around that time.

The January 2024 Intake in the UK provides an excellent opportunity for international students who missed the Fall intake or need more time to prepare their applications. With the application window open between June and September 2023, students have enough time to gather the required documentation and apply to their preferred universities and colleges. FAQ

How many intakes are offered to study in the UK?

Three intakes are offered to study in the UK: September, January, and May.

When to apply for January 2024 Intake in the UK?

The application process for the January 2024 Intake in the UK begins from September 2023 to November 2023.

What is the other name for the January 2024 Intake in the UK?

The January 2024 Intake in the UK is also known as the Winter Intake.

Is Septemeber Intake better than the January Intake to study in the UK?

The September Intake offers a larger variety of courses, while the January Intake offers less competition than the September Intake.
